{{BLP sources|date=October 2011}} {{Infobox person | name = Ian Murdock | image = IanMurdock.jpg | image_size = 200px | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1973|04|28|df=yes}} | birth_place = [[Konstanz (district)|Konstanz]], [[West Germany]] | occupation = Programmer | residence = Indiana, USA | nationality = American | field = computer scientist, open source developer, entrepreneur | work_institutions = [[Sun Microsystems]] | alma_mater = [[Purdue University]] | known_for = [[Debian]] }} '''Ian Murdock''' (born April 28, 1973) is the founder of the [[Debian]] distribution and [[Progeny Linux Systems]], a commercial [[Linux]] company.
== Life and career ==
Murdock was born in [[Konstanz]], [[Germany]].
He wrote the [[Debian#1993â1998|Debian Manifesto]] in 1993 while a student at [[Purdue University]], where he earned his [[bachelor's degree]] in [[computer science]] in 1996. He named Debian after his then-girlfriend Debra Lynn, and himself (Deb and Ian).<ref>{{cite book |last = Nixon |first = Robin |title = Ubuntu: Up and Running |page = 3 |publisher = [[O'Reilly Media]] |year = 2010 |isbn = 9780596804848 |url = http://books.google.com/books?id=badSTnfeOoAC }}</ref>
On joining Sun, he led [[Project Indiana]], which he described as "taking the lesson that Linux has brought to the operating system and providing that for Solaris", making a full [[OpenSolaris]] distribution with [[GNOME]] and [[User space|userland]] tools from [[GNU]] plus a network-based package management system.<ref>{{citation | publisher = IT Jungle | url = http://www.itjungle.com/tug/tug080207-story01.html | title = The Unix Guardian | contribution = Q and A: Sun's Top Operating System Brass Talk OS Strategy}}.</ref> From March 2007 to February 2010, he was Vice President of Emerging Platforms at Sun, until the company merged with Oracle and he resigned his position with the company.<ref>{{citation | url = http://www.sun.com/aboutsun/media/ceo/bio.jsp?name=Ian%20Murdock | publisher = Sun | title = Executive Bio | contribution = Ian Murdock}}.</ref>
Murdock is currently Vice President of Platform and Developer Community at [[ExactTarget]], based in [[Indianapolis]].<ref>[http://www.linkedin.com/in/imurdock Ian Murdock Profile]. ''[[LinkedIn]].'' Retrieved on 2011-11-21.</ref>
